#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:77
msgid "Use the Windows menu to open the pane as a floating window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:79
msgid ""
"Click and drag its title bar to move it around and release to dock it "
"according to the highlighted insertion point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:81
msgid ""
"Trying to dock a pane to the leftmost/rightmost part of the interface may"
" fail if the main OpenToonz window is maximized at that moment. To "
"overcome this, you can restore the main window size, dock the desired "
"pane, and then maximize it back."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:83
msgid "**To remove a pane from a room:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:85
msgid ""
"Click and drag the title bar of the pane you want to remove to undock it "
"from the room."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:87
msgid "Close the floating window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:89
msgid "**To maximize, or minimize a maximized pane:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:91
msgid "Double-click its title bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:93
msgid ""
"Some panes like the toolbar and the level strip have some fixed size, "
"therefore they cannot be maximized."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:95
msgid "**To lock/unlock the rooms configuration:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:97
msgid "Activate/deactivate the Windows  →  Lock Room Panes option."
