#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:160
msgid "Flipbook"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:162
msgid "|UI_flipbook|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:164
msgid ""
"The flipbook can display animation levels, clips or sequences of images. "
"It can be used to check levels for instance before loading them, or to "
"control a rendered sequence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:166
msgid "See  :ref:`Using the Flipbook <using_the_flipbook>`  ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:172
msgid "Function Editor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:174
msgid "|UI_functioneditor|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:176
msgid ""
"The function editor maps objects and FX transformations with key values "
"and related interpolations by using a spreadsheet or a graph editor. It "
"is divided into two sections: on the left there is an area where the "
"spreadsheet or graph editor is displayed, on the right top is an area "
"where the interpolation of the current transformation segment is "
"displayed, and on the right bottom is the objects/FX tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:178
msgid "See  :ref:`Using the Function Editor <using_the_function_editor>`  ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:184
msgid "Level Strip"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:186
msgid "|UI_levelstrip|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:188
msgid ""
"The level strip displays the sequence of drawings belonging to the level "
"currently selected in the Xsheet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:190
msgid ""
"It helps you to edit the sequence of drawings and to see all the drawings"
" of the current level, even if those drawings are not exposed in a "
"Xsheet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:192
msgid "See  :ref:`Editing Animation Levels <editing_animation_levels>`  ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:198
msgid "Palette"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:200
msgid "|UI_palette|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:202
msgid ""
"It displays the styles defined for the current level, or in case it is "
"inactive the styles defined for a previously selected level."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:204
msgid "See  :ref:`The Palette Window <the_palette_window>`  ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:210
msgid "Scene Cast"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:212
msgid "|UI_scenecast|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:214
msgid ""
"The scene cast pane lets you control the files loaded in the scene, save "
"them and load new ones. It can be organized in folders and sub-folders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:216
msgid "See  :ref:`Using the Scene Cast <using_the_scene_cast>`  ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:222
msgid "Schematic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:224
msgid "|UI_schematic|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:226
msgid ""
"The schematic can alternatively display stage information or special FX "
"usage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:228
msgid ""
"The stage schematic displays as nodes all the objects defined in a scene,"
" i.e. columns, pegbars, cameras, the table and motion paths, and allows "
"you to manage the way they are linked to each other."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:230
msgid ""
"The FX schematic allows you to apply FX to the content of Xsheet columns,"
" and to manage the way they are applied. All the columns and FX are "
"displayed as nodes that can be connected in order to set the way FX "
"affect the scene content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:232
msgid ""
"See  :ref:`Using the Stage Schematic <using_the_stage_schematic>`  and  "
":ref:`Using the FX Schematic <using_the_fx_schematic>`  ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:238
msgid "Studio Palette"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:240
msgid "|UI_studiopalette|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:242
msgid ""
"The studio palette allows you to store an unlimited number of level "
"palettes. From here any palette can be retrieved and assigned to the "
"current level in order to paint it, with no need to define the same "
"styles again and again. It also includes a viewer displaying the styles "
"of the currently selected palette."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:244
msgid "See  :ref:`Using the Studio Palette <using_the_studio_palette>`  ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:250
msgid "Style Editor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:252
msgid "|UI_styleeditor|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:254
msgid ""
"The style editor allows you to modify the palette styles. You can choose "
"the type of style among color, texture, vector and raster. There also is "
"a settings tab where you can decide some parameters for the style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:256
msgid "See  :ref:`Editing Styles <editing_styles>`  ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:262
msgid "Tasks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:264
msgid "|UI_tasks|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:266
msgid ""
"The Tasks window contains the task tree with all the tasks submitted to "
"the batch processing, and information about the task currently selected "
"in the tree. From the task tree you can start or stop a task execution, "
"or remove it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:268
msgid ""
"See  :ref:`Managing and Executing Render Tasks "
"<managing_and_executing_render_tasks>`  ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:274
msgid "Message Center"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:276
msgid "|UI_messagecenter|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:278
msgid ""
"The message center displays in a list the messages OpenToonz is sending "
"to the user. You can set filters on the messages showed in the window "
"using the appropriate radio buttons, or you can clear completely the list"
" pressing the Clear button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:284
msgid "Toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:286
msgid "|UI_toolbar|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:288
msgid ""
"The toolbar contains tools to draw, select and edit drawings, and to "
"animate objects like the camera, columns and pegbars. The tools in the "
"toolbar can only be used in the main viewer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:290
msgid ""
"If the toolbar is too short to display all the tools, it can be scrolled "
"by using arrow buttons available at its ends."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:292
msgid ""
"|animate| **Animate** modifies the position, rotation and size of the "
"current objects (see  :ref:`Animating Objects <animating_objects>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:297
msgid ""
"|selection| **Selection** performs a selection and transforms it (see  "
":ref:`Using the Selection Tool <using_the_selection_tool>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:302
msgid ""
"|brush| **Brush** draws in the work area in freehand mode (see  "
":ref:`Drawing with the Brush Tool <drawing_with_the_brush_tool>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:307
msgid ""
"|geometric| **Geometric** draws geometric shapes (see  :ref:`Drawing with"
" the Geometric Tool <drawing_with_the_geometric_tool>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:312
msgid ""
"|type| **Type** adds text by setting the font and size (see  :ref:`Adding"
" Text <adding_text>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:317
msgid ""
"|fill| **Fill** fills drawing areas with the current style (see  "
":ref:`Filling Areas <filling_areas>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:322
msgid ""
"|paint_brush| **Paint Brush** paints lines and areas in Toonz raster "
"drawings in freehand mode. (see  :ref:`Filling Areas <filling_areas>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:327
msgid ""
"|eraser| **Eraser** deletes vectors in vector drawings, and painted areas"
" and lines in raster drawings (see  :ref:`Drawing Tools <drawing_tools>`"
"  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:332
msgid ""
"|tape| **Tape** joins two open ends of one or two vectors in vector "
"drawings, or closes gaps in raster drawings (see  :ref:`Joining and "
"Splitting <joining_and_splitting>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:337
msgid ""
"|style_picker| **Style Picker** picks a style from the current drawing, "
"that becomes the current style in the palette and in the style editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:342
msgid ""
"|RGB_picker| **RGB Picker** picks red, green and blue values from the "
"viewer content, and applies them to the current style (see  :ref:`Plain "
"Colors <plain_colors>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:347
msgid ""
"|cpe| **Control Point Editor** modifies the vector shape by editing its "
"control points (see  :ref:`Editing Vector Control Points "
"<editing_vector_control_points>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:352
msgid ""
"|pinch| **Pinch** modifies the vector shape by clicking and dragging "
"anywhere on the vector (see  :ref:`Changing the Bend of Vectors "
"<changing_the_bend_of_vectors>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:357
msgid ""
"|pump| **Pump** locally modifies the vector thickness by clicking on the "
"section you want to affect and then dragging up or down (see  :ref:`Using"
" Other Modifier Tools <using_other_modifier_tools>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:362
msgid ""
"|magnet| **Magnet** deforms several vectors at once by clicking the area "
"you want to affect and dragging (see  :ref:`Using Other Modifier Tools "
"<using_other_modifier_tools>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:367
msgid ""
"|bender| **Bender** bends vectors in vector drawings (see  :ref:`Using "
"Other Modifier Tools <using_other_modifier_tools>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:372
msgid ""
"|iron| **Iron** removes creases from vectors by moving the cursor on the "
"vector you want to flatten (see  :ref:`Using Other Modifier Tools "
"<using_other_modifier_tools>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:377
msgid ""
"|cutter| **Cutter** splits a vector in two sections when clicking on it "
"(see  :ref:`Joining and Splitting <joining_and_splitting>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:382
msgid ""
"|skeleton| **Skeleton** defines character models, and animates them as in"
" cutout animation (see  :ref:`Using the Skeleton Tool "
"<using_the_skeleton_tool>`  )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:387
msgid ""
"|hook| **Hook** defines reference points to be used in the stage "
"schematic to move an object, or link one object to another (see  "
":ref:`Using Hooks <using_hooks>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:392
msgid ""
"|tracker| **Tracker** tracks specific regions in a sequence of images "
"(see  :ref:`Tracking Points <tracking_points>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:397
msgid ""
"|plastic| **Plastic** builds a mesh that allows to deform and animate a "
"character or part of it (see  :ref:`Using Plastic tool "
"<using_plastic_tool>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:402
msgid ""
"|zoom| **Zoom** zooms in and out the viewer content; after you click you "
"can drag up to zoom in the work area, or drag down to zoom out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:407
msgid ""
"|hand| **Hand** pans over the viewer content; if the 3D view is "
"activated, the Hand tool lets you pan over the 3D view as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:412
msgid ""
"|rotate| **Rotate** rotates the viewer content; if the 3D view is "
"activated, the Rotate tool lets you change the point of view."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:418
msgid "Tool Options Bar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:420
msgid "|UI_tooloptionsbar|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:422
msgid ""
"The tool options bar displays settings for the current tool, if it has "
"any."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:424
msgid ""
"For example it lets you set the thickness and other properties of the "
"Brush tool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:426
msgid ""
"If the tool options bar is too short to display all the tool options, it "
"can be scrolled by using arrow buttons available at its ends."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:432
msgid "Command Bar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:434
msgid "|UI_commandbar|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:436
msgid ""
"The Command Bar is a place where the user can display favorite OpenToonz "
"tools and commands to have them readily available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:438
msgid "The Command Bar pane can be docked in any part of the OpenToonz UI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:440
msgid ""
"If the Command Bar is too short to display all the command buttons, a "
"double-arrow symbol will appear at the right end of it, allowing to "
"display a drop down menu with the rest of them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:442
msgid "**To display the Command Bar:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:444
msgid "Choose Windows  →  Command Bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:446
msgid "**To customize the Command Bar buttons:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:448
msgid "Choose Windows  →  Command Bar to open the Command Bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:450
msgid ""
"Right click on it and select **Customize Command Bar** from the menu that"
" opens. The Customize Command Bar window will open."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:452
msgid "|UI_commandbar_window|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:454
msgid ""
"To *add* a command: Search for a command in the **Toolbar Items** list "
"(right) and drag it to the **Command Bar** list (left)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:456
msgid ""
"To *add* a separator: At the end of the **Toolbar Items** list (right), "
"drag the **----Separator----** item to the **Command Bar** list (left)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:458
msgid ""
"To *delete* a command: Locate the command in the **Command Bar** list "
"(left), right click on it and select **Remove** from the menu that opens."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:460
msgid "Click **OK** to accept the changes or **Cancel** to discard them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:466
msgid "Viewer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:468
msgid "|UI_viewer|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:470
msgid ""
"The viewer is the work area where you can draw images and see at the same"
" time the result of your compositing. It is endless and you can scroll, "
"zoom in, zoom out and rotate it the way you prefer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:472
#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:487
msgid ""
"It has different modes of visualization among which you can choose the "
"more suitable to the operation you are performing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:474
#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:489
msgid ""
"See  :ref:`Using the Viewer <using_the_work_area>`  and  :ref:`Previewing"
" the Animation <previewing_the_animation>`  ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:480
msgid "ComboViewer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:482
msgid "|UI_comboviewer|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:484
msgid ""
"The comboviewer integrates in a single pane a viewer, horizontal toolbar "
"and a tool options bar. It's and alternative work area where you can draw"
" images and see at the same time the result of your compositing. It is "
"endless and you can scroll, zoom in, zoom out and rotate it the way you "
"prefer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:495
msgid "Xsheet"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:497
msgid "|UI_xsheet|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:499
msgid ""
"The Xsheet allows you to manage the scene content, in the same manner as "
"the timeline. It is organized in columns, and columns are divided into "
"cells, representing the content of that column in that particular frame. "
"In the columns you can load animation levels, clips, images, audio files "
"or other Xsheets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:501
msgid ""
"Each column has its own header containing information about its content. "
"The column on the far left displays the frame number, with a cursor "
"placed on the current frame. The headers area and the frame column are "
"always visible, even when scrolling the Xsheet area; in this way it's "
"easier to understand how the scene is built."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/interface_overview.rst:503
msgid "Frames are rendered reading images from left to right in each cell row."
msgstr ""

